  "response": "Several key factors led to World War II:\n\n1. Treaty of Versailles (1919)\n- Harsh penalties on Germany after World War I\n- Severe economic reparations\n- Loss of territory\n- Created resentment and economic hardship in Germany\n\n2. Rise of Fascism and Nazism\n- Adolf Hitler's rise to power in Germany\n- Nazi ideology of racial superiority\n- Aggressive expansionist policies\n- Violation of the Versailles Treaty\n\n3. Economic Factors\n- Great Depression (1929)\n- Global economic instability\n- High unemployment\n- Economic desperation in many countries\n\n4. Expansionist Ambitions\n- Germany's desire to reclaim lost territories\n- Italy's ambitions under Mussolini\n- Japan's imperial expansion in Asia\n\n5. Failure of the League of Nations\n- Inability to prevent international conflicts\n- Weak diplomatic mechanisms\n- Lack of collective security\n\n6. Immediate Trigger\n- Germany's invasion of Poland on September 1, 1939\n- Britain and France declaring war on Germany in response\n\nThese complex interconnected factors created conditions that ultimately led to the outbreak of World War II, which became a global conflict involving most of the world's nations.",
